terms.medium_def:
A Judge living before Israel's Monarchy, first mentioned at Jdg.6.11; 
referred to as Gideon (גִּדְעוֹן), or Jerubbaal (יְרֻבַּ֫עַל), or Jerubbesheth (יְרֻבֶּשֶׁת), or Gideon (Γεδεών); 
a son of Joash; 
father of Jether, Abimelech and Jotham. § name given to Gideon by his father when he destroyed the altar of Baal

Jonathan's son from the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Sa.4.4; 
referred to as Mephibosheth (מְפִיבֹשֶׁת), or Merib-baal (מְרִיב בַּ֫עַל), or Merib-baal (מְרִי בַעַל); 
a son of Jonathan; 
father of Micah.

A location near Kadesh-barnea first mentioned at Num.20.13; 
referred to as Meribah (מְרִיבָה), or Meribah/-kadesh (KJV= "strife in Kadesh") (מְרִיבָה קָדֵשׁ). § ♣1) a fountain at Rephidim, in the desert of Sin; so called because the Israelites murmured against God
2) the name of the water supply at Kadesh on the southern border of the promised land; the people also murmured here against God

Jonathan's son from the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Sa.4.4; 
referred to as Mephibosheth (מְפִיבֹשֶׁת), or Merib-baal (מְרִיב בַּ֫עַל), or Merib-baal (מְרִי בַעַל); 
a son of Jonathan; 
father of Micah.

A man living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Sa.23.29; 
only referred to as Ribai (רִיבַי); 
father of Ittai. § father of Ittai the Benjamite of Gibeah

A Judge living before Israel's Monarchy, first mentioned at Jdg.6.11; 
referred to as Gideon (גִּדְעוֹן), or Jerubbaal (יְרֻבַּ֫עַל), or Jerubbesheth (יְרֻבֶּשֶׁת), or Gideon (Γεδεών); 
a son of Joash; 
father of Jether, Abimelech and Jotham. § a variant name of Jerubbaal ) substituting the word 'shame' for the name of the pagan god 'Baal'

A man from the tribe of Simeon living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.10; 
referred to as Jachin (יָכִין), or Jachinite (יָכִינִי), or Jarib (יָרִיב); 
son of Simeon; 
a brother of Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Zerah and Shaul.

A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.11.46; 
only referred to as Jeribai (יְרִיבַי); 
son of Elnaam; 
a brother of Joshaviah. § a descendant of Elnaam and one of David's mighty warriors

A man from the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of United Monarchy, only mentioned at 2Sa.21.8; 
only referred to as Mephibosheth (מְפִיבֹשֶׁת); 
son of Saul and Rizpah; 
a brother of Armoni; 
half-brother of: Jonathan, Abinadab, Malchi-shua, Merab, Michal and Ish-bosheth.

Jonathan's son from the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Sa.4.4; 
referred to as Mephibosheth (מְפִיבֹשֶׁת), or Merib-baal (מְרִיב בַּ֫עַל), or Merib-baal (מְרִי בַעַל); 
a son of Jonathan; 
father of Micah.

A location in Edom first mentioned at Gen.36.35; 
referred to as Midian or Midianite (מִדְיָן), or Midianite woman (מִדְיָנִי), or Midianite (מְדָנִי), or Midian (Μαδιάν). § the tribe descended from Midian
inhabitant of the territory of the tribe descended from Midian; located principally in the desert north of the Arabian peninsula; land to which Moses went when he fled from Pharaoh

Jacob's daughter living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.30.21; 
only referred to as Dinah (דִּינָה); 
daughter of Israel and Leah; 
a sister of Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar and Zebulun; 
half-sister of: Dan, Naphtali, Gad, Asher, Joseph and Benjamin. § daughter of Jacob by Leah, full sister of Simeon and Levi

Jacob's son who founded the tribe of Dan living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.30.6; 
only referred to as Dan (דָּן); 
son of Israel and Bilhah; 
a brother of Naphtali; 
half-brother of: Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Gad, Asher, Issachar, Zebulun, Dinah, Joseph and Benjamin; 
father of Hushim.

A location in Dan Tribe first mentioned at Gen.14.14; 
referred to as Dan or Danite (דָּן), or Dan or Danite (דָּנִי), or Laish (לַ֫יִשׁ), or Leshem (לֶ֫שֶׁם). § ♣1) descendants of Dan, son of Jacob
2) inhabitants of the territory of Dan

A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.25.2; 
only referred to as Midian (מִדְיָן); 
son of Abraham and Keturah; 
half-brother of: Ishmael and Isaac; 
a brother of Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Ishbak and Shuah; 
father of Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida and Eldaah.

A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.25.2; 
only referred to as Medan (מְדָן); 
son of Abraham and Keturah; 
half-brother of: Ishmael and Isaac; 
a brother of Zimran, Jokshan, Midian, Ishbak and Shuah. § a son of Abraham by Keturah

David's son from the tribe of Judah living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Sa.3.3; 
referred to as Chileab (כִּלְאָב), or Daniel (דָּנִיֵּאל, דָּנִאֵל); 
a son of David and Abigail; 
half-brother of: Amnon, Absalom, Adonijah, Shephatiah, Ithream, Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon, Ibhar, Elishua, Nepheg, Japhia, Elishama, Eliada, Eliphelet, Tamar, Elpelet, Nogah and Jerimoth.

A man of the Gomerians living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.10.3; 
referred to as Riphath (רִיפַת), or Riphath (דִּיפַת); 
son of Gomer; 
a brother of Ashkenaz and Togarmah. § the 2nd son of Gomer

A man of the Gomerians living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.10.3; 
referred to as Riphath (רִיפַת), or Riphath (דִּיפַת); 
son of Gomer; 
a brother of Ashkenaz and Togarmah. § the 2nd son of Gomer

A location near Bethlehem only mentioned at Jer.41.17; 
only referred to as Geruth_Chimham (גֵּרוּת כְּמוֹ). § 
This name means lodging place
